Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a red pottery vessel, the fabric is relatively coarse and contains many small white inclusions, the exterior is covered with a light brown slip and remains of three lines of black-painted demotic text.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Osireion (Abydos), Temenos Wall (south of) West Trench 16.I.26
Bibliographic references: Frankfort 1933 / The Cenotaph of Seti I at Abydos (no. 6 (p.95,pl.xciii))
Jasnow & Pouls Wegner 2006-2007 / Demotic Ostraca from North Abydos (p. 51 no. 6.)
Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (51780) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/51780)
